Former New York Giants Receiver Steve Smith Signs With Philadelphia Eagles

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-08-11T01:13:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/former-new-york-giants-receiver-steve-smith-signs-with-philadelphia-eagles.html
Wide receiver  Steve Smith , a former
 Pro Bowl  selection from the  New York Giants , signed a one-year
free-agent contract today with the  Philadelphia Eagles .  Smith, 26, spent the first four seasons of his NFL career
with the Giants, catching 220 passes for 2,386 yards and 11
touchdowns. He was selected for the Pro Bowl after a 2009 season
in which he set a team record with 107 receptions.  Smith was limited by a knee injury to nine games and 48
receptions last season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  